WEBVTT

00:04.944 --> 00:07.613
Keep your eyes steadily on the disc.

00:07.614 --> 00:10.949
But it's getting harder.

00:10.984 --> 00:14.853
Your eyes are so tired from staring.

00:14.854 --> 00:18.356
Your eyelids feel like lead.

00:18.357 --> 00:20.892
They want to close.

00:20.893 --> 00:25.130
Heavier. Heavier.

00:25.131 --> 00:27.899
You must close them...

00:27.900 --> 00:29.935
now.

00:33.039 --> 00:35.072
Ladies and gentlemen,

00:35.174 --> 00:38.309
these three people are
now in a state of hypnosis.

00:38.377 --> 00:41.979
Suggestions I make will
be implicitly accepted

00:42.014 --> 00:44.549
regardless of their nonsensical character.

00:52.324 --> 00:54.359
Archie.

00:54.360 --> 00:57.828
Archie, when you wake,

00:57.863 --> 01:01.265
there will be a kitten in front of you.

01:01.399 --> 01:05.770
There is nothing more frightening
in this world than this creature.

01:05.771 --> 01:08.538
You want nothing to do with it.

01:13.679 --> 01:15.712
No!

01:15.713 --> 01:17.613
No, get... no kitties!

01:17.614 --> 01:19.748
It's only a kitten.

01:19.750 --> 01:21.284
Get the cat out of here!

01:21.285 --> 01:23.753
Gonna kill us all! Get it out!

01:31.929 --> 01:33.963
They come from Siberia,

01:33.964 --> 01:37.332
a fierce and dangerous place.

01:37.366 --> 01:39.467
Their mother, when she was with child,

01:39.468 --> 01:41.870
was attacked by a bear.

01:41.905 --> 01:44.272
The girls, even in their mother's womb,

01:44.440 --> 01:48.043
instinctively knew that to survive
they should cling to one another.

01:48.044 --> 01:50.478
They held on so tight,

01:50.479 --> 01:53.581
and this was the result.

01:53.583 --> 01:55.784
The birth was so excruciating,

01:55.785 --> 01:58.086
it killed their mother.

01:58.154 --> 02:01.389
Their father died of
shock upon seeing them.

02:01.390 --> 02:05.059
Zoya and Nika were alone.

02:05.060 --> 02:07.194
But they proved in the womb

02:07.230 --> 02:09.830
their incredible survival ability.

02:09.832 --> 02:12.500
They lived off the milk of a goat

02:12.501 --> 02:15.069
and fallen acorns from a tree.

02:15.170 --> 02:19.473
They watched the wolves and
by the age of four could hunt.

02:19.475 --> 02:23.277
They taught themselves to speak, to sing,

02:23.346 --> 02:27.448
and even to play instruments
that they carved themselves.

02:29.000 --> 02:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:49.671 --> 02:51.838
That's quite a story.

02:51.839 --> 02:53.840
I've recounted it 1,000 times

02:53.841 --> 02:55.841
and I still find it inspiring.

02:55.977 --> 02:59.345
How would you know that they
clung to each other in the womb?

02:59.346 --> 03:01.181
You telling me my business, mister?

03:01.182 --> 03:03.049
No, no, no. I meant no disrespect.

03:03.050 --> 03:05.218
I'm a doctor. I'm a natural skeptic.

03:05.219 --> 03:07.520
John Thackery. Knickerbocker Hospital.

03:07.521 --> 03:09.622
Lester Brockhurst.

03:09.791 --> 03:13.794
Mr. Brockhurst, would you be willing
to allow me to examine the girls?

03:13.795 --> 03:15.095
What for?

03:15.129 --> 03:18.531
Purely from a scientific perspective.

03:18.565 --> 03:20.533
When was the last time they saw a doctor?

03:20.634 --> 03:23.169
I got a physician's book.
I make sure they're healthy.

03:23.304 --> 03:26.606
No, of course. And it looks
like you're doing a fine job.

03:26.707 --> 03:29.642
One of them got dysentery
last year. I fixed her up.

03:29.643 --> 03:32.111
That's very impressive.

03:32.145 --> 03:35.014
So they don't share a digestive tract.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.718
It's not that I don't trust doctors,

03:38.719 --> 03:39.885
it's the time it takes.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.487
That's money out of my pocket.

03:43.557 --> 03:47.392
So, what would you say if I offered
to hire them for a private show?

03:48.495 --> 03:50.129
We'll need transportation

03:50.197 --> 03:53.699
and a meal afterwards for
me at a reputable place.

03:53.701 --> 03:56.535
That can definitely be arranged.

03:56.536 --> 03:58.236
I'll be in touch.

04:08.461 --> 04:12.568
Subtitle sync and corrections
by awaqeded for www.addic7ed.com.

04:32.704 --> 04:34.838
Morphine for the pain.

04:35.039 --> 04:39.143
The nurse will take you to another
room to rest for a couple of hours.

04:39.210 --> 04:42.546
The X-rays will have
been developed by then.

04:42.614 --> 04:45.282
I'll come in and check
on you and take you home.

05:00.499 --> 05:02.633
Do those help?

05:02.634 --> 05:05.202
A little.

05:05.303 --> 05:08.971
The key seems to be in coating
the zinc needles with mercury.

05:08.973 --> 05:10.540
And the amount of current needed

05:10.574 --> 05:12.242
for the zinc and mercury to ionize

05:12.277 --> 05:14.043
is dependent upon the size of the tumor.

05:14.279 --> 05:17.113
But if done correctly, the procedure
claims to kill all the malignant cells

05:17.148 --> 05:18.682
without disturbing the healthy tissue.

05:18.783 --> 05:21.551
It seems far less risky
than an all-out laryngectomy.

05:21.652 --> 05:24.221
I witnessed several of those
in Paris. They all failed.

05:24.255 --> 05:25.788
They couldn't reconstruct the windpipe

05:25.856 --> 05:28.391
after having removed so
much tissue with the tumor.

05:30.828 --> 05:33.330
I think it's worth trying.

05:33.331 --> 05:35.998
In the absence of any other solution, yes.

05:36.100 --> 05:38.367
But it's still experimental
and Zinberg would never...

05:38.469 --> 05:41.971
I don't have the luxury of
two years' worth of study.

05:41.972 --> 05:44.207
So I was hoping you'd help me.

05:45.342 --> 05:47.409
You have experience working in secret.

05:48.979 --> 05:51.180
I'm sorry.

05:51.181 --> 05:54.416
I just meant I need someone I can trust.

05:54.485 --> 05:57.553
Harold. Harold. Just tell Croker

05:57.588 --> 06:00.422
he'll have the last 100,000 by Tuesday.

06:01.459 --> 06:03.092
Right.

06:03.193 --> 06:06.462
And listen, Harold. Where are
we with the Brooklyn lines?

06:06.497 --> 06:08.197
'Cause I don't want to open the paper

06:08.198 --> 06:10.233
and find they've all been auctioned off.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.471
Uh-huh.

06:15.472 --> 06:17.606
Right.

06:17.607 --> 06:19.275
That's fine.

06:19.309 --> 06:22.144
Just keep me apprised of the situation.

06:22.179 --> 06:24.680
All right, I have to go, Prettyman.

06:24.681 --> 06:26.282
Good-bye.

06:28.118 --> 06:30.019
Nurse Elkins.

06:30.020 --> 06:33.689
What are you...

06:35.359 --> 06:37.225
I've been watching some of the other girls

06:37.361 --> 06:40.695
receive invitations to the
fundraising ball from their suitors.

06:43.366 --> 06:45.400
I was wondering when I was gonna get mine.

06:48.971 --> 06:52.640
How many other girls
do I have to watch smile

06:52.674 --> 06:56.011
holding an invitation before I get one?

06:56.012 --> 06:58.379
I...

07:01.083 --> 07:03.884
Usually you have so many
clever things to say.

07:05.186 --> 07:07.554
What's the matter?

07:08.590 --> 07:10.391
People can see.

07:10.392 --> 07:12.159
The glass.

07:12.193 --> 07:14.962
Doesn't bother me. Does it bother you?

07:18.066 --> 07:20.768
Maybe I should stop so you
can gather your thoughts.

07:20.769 --> 07:23.738
No.

07:23.739 --> 07:27.741
Well, then, my invitation?

07:28.943 --> 07:30.777
Soon.

07:30.778 --> 07:33.380
Very soon.

07:36.518 --> 07:38.318
Good.

07:45.293 --> 07:48.128
And this is the big top

07:48.129 --> 07:50.563
at the center of our circus.

07:52.232 --> 07:54.299
How full does your gallery get?

07:54.301 --> 07:56.802
When Thackery was leading the operations,

07:56.803 --> 07:59.271
standing room only.

07:59.273 --> 08:03.542
Not what yours is, is it, Russell?

08:05.279 --> 08:09.348
Well, we don't have the suction machine

08:09.383 --> 08:11.616
or any of the other electric gadgets.

08:11.618 --> 08:13.118
Lighting is better in here, too.

08:13.119 --> 08:15.187
Mm-hmm.

08:15.221 --> 08:18.958
I'm sure yours will still suffice.

08:18.959 --> 08:20.859
For what?

08:25.799 --> 08:28.934
Carr needs surgery.

08:28.935 --> 08:30.635
Umbilical hernia.

08:30.737 --> 08:34.905
Had it for years, but I need
to have it taken care of.

08:34.907 --> 08:37.142
I've read your hernia paper.

08:37.143 --> 08:38.809
I thought I'd do it for him.

08:38.811 --> 08:40.477
My procedure?

08:40.513 --> 08:43.280
Russell says he's read
the paper thoroughly.

08:43.282 --> 08:46.551
But he's never performed it.

08:46.586 --> 08:48.320
And you'd be doing this at your place?

08:48.321 --> 08:49.953
Of course he would.

08:49.954 --> 08:52.723
We couldn't do it here.

08:55.327 --> 08:57.594
There are rules.

09:01.133 --> 09:03.734
I was thinking,

09:03.735 --> 09:06.036
and no disrespect to you, Russell,

09:06.037 --> 09:07.370
but since I did invent the procedure,

09:07.405 --> 09:10.307
perhaps I should be the one to perform it.

09:12.677 --> 09:14.678
Of course.

09:14.679 --> 09:16.713
You were the first choice.

09:20.718 --> 09:23.053
And we should do it here

09:23.054 --> 09:25.155
if we can.

09:25.156 --> 09:27.490
I'll ask Thackery.

09:27.525 --> 09:30.360
See if he can square it with the board.

09:30.361 --> 09:32.996
Then we'll wait to hear from you.

09:36.433 --> 09:38.901
- Hello?
- We're in here.

09:41.438 --> 09:43.206
Sorry I'm late.

09:43.240 --> 09:45.041
It's quite all right. We waited to eat.

09:45.043 --> 09:48.111
Good evening, Dr. Gallinger.

09:48.112 --> 09:49.946
What are you doing here?

09:50.048 --> 09:53.183
Your wife graciously invited me to dinner.

09:54.518 --> 09:57.953
Why would you invite
Dr. Cotton into our home?

09:57.954 --> 10:00.223
To thank him for what he did for me.

10:00.224 --> 10:01.957
For us.

10:01.958 --> 10:04.226
He's the reason I feel the way I do.

10:04.295 --> 10:07.563
I am very pleased with
how Eleanor's been doing.

10:07.598 --> 10:09.158
I was just saying before you walked in,

10:09.233 --> 10:11.367
I think she might be mentally
fit to have children again.

10:11.368 --> 10:14.670
Isn't that wonderful, darling?

10:17.274 --> 10:18.808
The hospital's been doing so well,

10:18.875 --> 10:21.043
the state of New Jersey
has asked us to expand.

10:21.078 --> 10:23.479
We've seen patients
from across the country,

10:23.480 --> 10:25.114
several from as far away as Europe.

10:25.216 --> 10:28.584
Lucky for you that preying on
the desperate is so lucrative.

10:28.652 --> 10:31.253
Everett, I will not have
you insult our guest.

10:31.254 --> 10:32.654
That's all right, Eleanor.

10:32.655 --> 10:34.323
A man's entitled to his opinion,

10:34.324 --> 10:36.125
misinformed as it may be.

10:36.126 --> 10:39.128
Misinformed?

10:39.129 --> 10:41.863
You mutilated my wife.

10:41.898 --> 10:45.267
And yet here you sit with your wife,

10:45.335 --> 10:48.003
a wonderful host who's
prepared this delicious meal.

10:48.105 --> 10:50.406
Six months ago, you dreamed
of an evening like this.

10:50.440 --> 10:52.808
You think so? Then you're misinformed.

10:55.145 --> 10:57.245
Excuse me.

10:57.246 --> 11:00.081
Let me give you an example.

11:00.116 --> 11:02.450
We had one young man, suffered terribly

11:02.451 --> 11:03.984
his entire life from paranoia.

11:03.986 --> 11:06.521
Distrust of others. He heard voices.

11:06.655 --> 11:09.490
He was a hypochondriac to the
point where he couldn't function

11:09.524 --> 11:11.892
due to his own preoccupation with himself.

11:11.961 --> 11:15.529
Now, as with Eleanor, I
knew sepsis was the cause,

11:15.530 --> 11:17.865
so I removed his teeth at once.

11:17.867 --> 11:19.867
There was little change at first,

11:19.869 --> 11:22.703
but I owed it to this young man to help.

11:22.771 --> 11:25.072
And so I removed his
tonsils and his gallbladder.

11:25.173 --> 11:28.342
Now the distrust disappeared.

11:28.343 --> 11:30.377
So I kept on.

11:30.512 --> 11:33.514
In the end, his spleen, colon,
and testicles, they all came out.

11:33.515 --> 11:35.348
Dear God.

11:37.486 --> 11:40.120
I realize it may seem extreme,

11:40.188 --> 11:44.391
but I'm happy to report
the young man is now home,

11:44.526 --> 11:47.694
he's found employment, no longer
struggles with his symptoms.

11:47.728 --> 11:49.762
He is leading a relatively normal life.

11:49.864 --> 11:51.865
And five years ago, that
would have been impossible.

11:51.866 --> 11:53.600
Normal life?

11:53.668 --> 11:56.536
That young man isn't
a hypochondriac anymore

11:56.671 --> 11:59.539
'cause there's nothing left of
him to be hypochondriacal about.

11:59.540 --> 12:02.275
I don't understand why a doctor

12:02.376 --> 12:04.511
would shrink so timidly from
the frontiers of science.

12:04.512 --> 12:06.413
Is that so?

12:06.414 --> 12:09.349
Are you all right?

12:09.350 --> 12:11.217
I'm not feeling well.

12:11.218 --> 12:13.319
Where is your lavatory?

12:13.386 --> 12:17.323
Please, it's just up the
stairs and to the left.

12:28.401 --> 12:30.502
You really don't need to be so rude.

12:30.503 --> 12:31.937
He's our guest.

12:31.939 --> 12:34.039
Why did you invite him into our home?

12:34.040 --> 12:35.841
I could kill him.

12:35.875 --> 12:37.543
Perhaps you could just remove his teeth.

12:39.846 --> 12:41.447
Without anesthetic.

12:42.849 --> 12:44.950
I wanted him here.

12:45.084 --> 12:48.754
And you will both please try to
remain civil throughout dessert.

12:50.423 --> 12:52.390
I don't have an appetite.

13:13.812 --> 13:15.913
I'm sorry, Mrs. Gallinger.

13:15.982 --> 13:18.716
I am going to get on
home. I'm not feeling well.

13:18.717 --> 13:21.552
I'm so sorry to hear that.

13:21.553 --> 13:24.155
But I'm very glad that you came

13:24.290 --> 13:27.992
so that I could show you my
appreciation for what you did for me.

13:27.993 --> 13:29.459
Of course.

13:29.460 --> 13:31.061
Good night.

13:50.447 --> 13:52.315
Are you ready?

14:00.690 --> 14:02.891
I'll do my best, Mother.

14:07.164 --> 14:09.865
I love you, my darling.

14:09.866 --> 14:11.834
I'll see you when you wake up.

14:28.517 --> 14:30.518
Do you need a drape?

14:31.887 --> 14:35.157
No, she's a patient. She needs a surgeon.

14:35.158 --> 14:36.858
I'm a surgeon.

14:52.507 --> 14:54.308
Thank you.

15:20.734 --> 15:23.403
Right, hand me the electrodes.

15:24.771 --> 15:27.206
Make sure and contact the zinc and mercury

15:27.208 --> 15:28.874
that's been injected into the tumor

15:28.942 --> 15:31.344
in order to ensure that
ionization is complete

15:31.345 --> 15:33.879
and the cancer cells are killed.

15:35.716 --> 15:38.217
You did a nice job with these.

15:38.419 --> 15:41.586
When this is over, I'm gonna have these
melted down into a necklace for her

15:41.587 --> 15:44.189
to cover the scar.

15:44.190 --> 15:46.425
1,000 milliamperes.

15:55.402 --> 15:59.471
Three, two, one.

16:19.591 --> 16:21.759
All right.

16:23.495 --> 16:25.763
Any change?

16:25.764 --> 16:28.065
It should shrink and soften.

16:32.136 --> 16:34.704
We'll have to go again. Increase
the milliamperes to 1,200.

16:35.839 --> 16:38.040
What's going on?

16:38.109 --> 16:40.510
It's all right. I'm a
surgeon here. Dr. Chickering.

16:40.644 --> 16:43.713
There's no surgery scheduled
for tonight and no emergencies.

16:43.747 --> 16:45.115
You're not supposed to be in here.

16:45.116 --> 16:46.716
Yes, I am!

16:48.086 --> 16:49.886
And what about him?

16:52.856 --> 16:54.457
I'm harder to explain.

16:55.960 --> 16:58.594
- Excuse me.
- It's all right. It's all right.

16:58.595 --> 17:01.096
You're against the clock now.

17:03.266 --> 17:04.700
What are you doing?

17:04.701 --> 17:06.702
The laryngectomy.

17:06.703 --> 17:08.637
The tumor is braided into her larynx,

17:08.637 --> 17:10.439
trachea, and esophagus.

17:10.440 --> 17:11.772
How do you expect to remove it?

17:11.773 --> 17:14.209
What do you suggest, then?

17:14.310 --> 17:18.146
Close her up and take a day
to consider your options.

17:18.147 --> 17:20.015
Options?

17:20.016 --> 17:21.348
We know what's gonna happen.

17:21.351 --> 17:23.118
She starves to death or asphyxiates

17:23.119 --> 17:24.986
or chokes on her own spit.

17:32.495 --> 17:33.975
That part of the tumor may come away,

17:34.030 --> 17:35.931
but it'll take too much
of the posterior mucosa.

17:36.032 --> 17:38.699
I'll shave it as closely as I
can, try to limit the damage.

17:38.701 --> 17:40.601
It's tumorous through and through.

17:40.670 --> 17:42.703
God damn it, there's no
windpipe to work with.

17:42.705 --> 17:44.439
It's all tumor. It's torn to bits.

17:44.473 --> 17:46.507
Holes everywhere. Her lips are blue.

17:46.509 --> 17:49.077
She's hypoxic.

17:49.178 --> 17:51.211
Dr. Chickering, what in
God's name are you doing?

17:51.246 --> 17:53.047
In God's name I'm trying to save my mother!

17:53.048 --> 17:55.182
I take full responsibility.

17:55.250 --> 17:57.317
And if you worked here,
that might be worth a damn.

17:57.318 --> 17:58.819
There's no repairing that ventricle.

17:58.854 --> 18:00.887
Just use the tissue to shore up that hole.

18:00.889 --> 18:02.889
Her breathing is becoming labored.

18:02.891 --> 18:04.191
What is Dr. Edwards doing here?

18:04.225 --> 18:05.705
He knew the procedure we were trying.

18:05.727 --> 18:07.094
Then why isn't he leading the surgery?

18:07.095 --> 18:08.429
I've lost sight in my left eye.

18:08.496 --> 18:10.364
It's only recently begun to improve a bit.

18:10.398 --> 18:13.833
So your assisting surgeon is half blind

18:13.868 --> 18:16.135
with no depth perception. Wonderful.

18:16.270 --> 18:19.405
If you would kindly excoriate
us later, we are in trouble here.

18:23.277 --> 18:25.211
Oh, my.

18:26.747 --> 18:29.748
Harvest some tissue from
below the thyroid cartilage

18:29.850 --> 18:32.385
and use that to patch the
space on the tracheal rings.

18:32.452 --> 18:34.920
- Can you see well enough to patch that space?
- Yes.

18:34.921 --> 18:39.358
Good. Now draw the tissue across.

18:39.426 --> 18:41.760
Don't worry yourself with
the cancerous section.

18:41.895 --> 18:44.262
You're just trying to give her
something to breathe through.

18:44.298 --> 18:47.433
Now hold it up against the anterior wall.

18:47.434 --> 18:49.368
I'll suture it.

18:50.870 --> 18:53.772
I'm not clean, but the instrument is.

18:53.773 --> 18:56.574
My patch is almost in.

18:56.710 --> 18:59.344
- She's still not getting any air.
- It's falling apart.

18:59.445 --> 19:01.579
It's shredding the edge of
the tumor near the subglottis.

19:01.581 --> 19:04.083
We need more tissue.

19:04.084 --> 19:06.018
She's cyanotic.

19:10.056 --> 19:11.990
There's no pulse.

19:12.058 --> 19:14.326
We can harvest from the soft palate

19:14.460 --> 19:17.095
and use it to cover the shredded
area near the subglottis.

19:19.165 --> 19:21.065
- Bertie.
- No.

19:22.801 --> 19:24.336
Let her go.

19:24.337 --> 19:26.838
She's been through enough.

19:26.839 --> 19:28.873
Let her go.

19:39.685 --> 19:43.054
Fuck.

19:43.155 --> 19:45.056
You're right, it could
never have succeeded.

19:45.157 --> 19:47.658
From the day she was
diagnosed, she was dead.

19:47.726 --> 19:51.562
It needed to be studied,
it needed to be perfected.

19:51.563 --> 19:54.198
But she was my mother.

19:54.199 --> 19:56.234
What was I supposed to do?

19:56.235 --> 19:59.170
I'm not running a circus.

19:59.171 --> 20:01.038
There are no high-wire acts here.

20:01.039 --> 20:03.006
But sometimes there needs to be.

20:03.008 --> 20:04.742
Sometimes risks have to be taken.

20:04.743 --> 20:07.378
Not in my operating rooms.

20:17.722 --> 20:19.690
I think it best if I resign.

20:24.262 --> 20:26.229
I agree.

20:28.032 --> 20:29.833
It'll save me the task
of having to fire you

20:29.834 --> 20:32.168
for violating protocols.

20:36.374 --> 20:38.508
Now go be with your family.

21:13.210 --> 21:15.377
I'm sorry.

21:18.281 --> 21:20.415
So am I.

21:26.824 --> 21:29.391
